    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-04T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-04T21:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760D.61/1550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-04T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 4, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. The Embassy at Moscow has recently reported to the Department a number of
                    comments appearing in the Soviet press concerning alleged economic distress in
                    Finland and contrasting particularly the unhappy lot of the Karelian refugees in
                    Finland with the fortunate lot of the peasants in the Baltic states. The former
                    are alleged to be roaming the streets and countryside of Finland in search of
                    food and work. The Embassy comments that the appearance of these articles may be
                    an attempt by the Soviet authorities to prepare the ground to further their aims
                    vis-à-vis Finland coincidental with a major move on the part of Germany against
                    England or in the Balkans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
